messages.content: What is the primary function of ComfyUI-FBCNN?
ComfyUI-FBCNN is a JPEG artifact/compression removal tool designed to work automatically or with user assistance.
ComfyUI-FBCNN can be downloaded or cloned into the ComfyUI/custom_nodes/ directory. It requires Pytorch, numpy, and requests, which should already be installed with ComfyUI.
Where can I find the ComfyUI-FBCNN node?
The ComfyUI-FBCNN node can be found under the 'image/upscaling' category in ComfyUI.
What input is needed for the ComfyUI-FBCNN model?
The ComfyUI-FBCNN model requires an estimate of the compression level as input, which is a number between 0 and 100.
What happens if I leave 'auto_detect' enabled in ComfyUI-FBCNN?
If 'auto_detect' is left enabled, the value of 'compression_level' will be ignored.
What libraries does ComfyUI-FBCNN depend on?
ComfyUI-FBCNN depends on Pytorch, numpy, and requests.
Can I set the compression level manually in ComfyUI-FBCNN?
Yes, you can manually set the compression level in ComfyUI-FBCNN by setting 'auto_detect' to 'disabled' and providing the value in 'compression_level'.
What happens if 'auto_detect' is set to 'enabled' and 'compression_level' is also provided?
If 'auto_detect' is set to 'enabled', the value of 'compression_level' will be ignored.
